25|$|Omaar {{has written}} a book about his time as the BBC's Iraq {{correspondent}} called Revolution Day. The book deals with the effects of the Saddam Hussein regime, UN sanctions, and of the war on <b>Iraqi</b> <b>civilians.</b>|$|E
25|$|In August 2015, Corbyn {{stated that}} if he became Labour leader, he would issue a public apology, {{on behalf of the}} Labour Party, for its role in the 2003 {{invasion}} of Iraq by Britain, and for the resulting deaths of 179 British soldiers and thousands of <b>Iraqi</b> <b>civilians.</b> Corbyn has also suggested that, should the Chilcot Inquiry find former Prime Minister Tony Blair guilty of war crimes, he should stand trial.|$|E
