500|$|In {{the battle}} for [...] "hearts and minds" [...] in Iraq, the Saltire was again used by the British Army {{as a means of}} {{distinguishing}} troops belonging to Scottish regiments from other coalition forces, in the hope of fostering better relations with the civilian population in the area south west of Baghdad. Leaflets were distributed to <b>Iraqi</b> <b>civilians,</b> by members of the Black Watch, depicting troops and vehicles set against a backdrop of the Saltire.|$|E
